snippet: Wall Street traded sharply higher after some cheery economic reports on unemployment and housing starts.
abstract: Standard & Poor's 500-stock index climbs to another five-year high after strong reports on housing starts and unemployment claims made investors more optimistic about nation’s economy.
lead_paragraph: Wall Street traded sharply higher after some cheery economic reports on unemployment and housing starts.

headline.main: Strong Economic Data Lifts S.&P. to 5-Year High
